definition.value: A quinolinium ion that is 1-methylquinolinium substituted by dimethylamino group at position 6 and a (E)-2-(2,5-dimethyl-1-phenyl-1H-pyrrol-3-yl)ethenyl at position 2. It is a  anthelminthic drug active against pinworms. The salts of pyrvinium can also be used as anticancer agents.
